premise_source_doc_sentence: Gabourey Sidibe  (  -LSB- ˈɡæbəˌreɪ_ˈsɪdɪˌbeɪ -RSB- ; born May 6 , 1983  )  is an American actress who made her acting debut in the 2009 film Precious , a role that brought her a nomination for the Academy Award for Best Actress .
From 2010 to 2013 , she was a main cast member of the Showtime series The Big C.

Sidibe co-starred on the television series American Horror Story : Coven as Queenie and American Horror Story : Freak Show as Regina Ross , and later reprised her role as Queenie in American Horror Story : Hotel .
Since 2015 , she stars in the Fox musical drama series Empire as Becky Williams .
